Sentencas: A micromodel based upon percolation theory is developed to predict effective properties in composite electrodes for solid oxide fuel-cell (SOFC) applications.
Titulo: Percolation theory to predict effective properties of solid oxide fuel-cell composite electrodes

Sentencas: The theory considers binary and multi-component mixtures of particles that are either ion or electron conductors.
Titulo: Percolation theory to predict effective properties of solid oxide fuel-cell composite electrodes

Sentencas: The model predicts effective ionic and electronic conductivities, three-phase boundary lengths, and hydraulic pore radii.
Titulo: Percolation theory to predict effective properties of solid oxide fuel-cell composite electrodes

Sentencas: The effective properties depend upon primary physical characteristics, including average particle-radii, volumetric packing densities, particle contact angles, and porosity.
Titulo: Percolation theory to predict effective properties of solid oxide fuel-cell composite electrodes

Sentencas: All results ate presented in nondimensional form, which provides considerable generality in their practical application.
